5:
Careful, Alk! You mustn't step in that
vile liquid...
9: Fear not. It no longer has any power.
12:
Out here, the spirits of the dead are
at the mercy of the light. They will
simply fade away over time.
20: Tell me, what was it you hoped to do?
22: Did you want to help your people?
26:
...You speak as if it were so simple.
Do you think you could have saved
them?
30:
Save them? No. That is not within my
power to do.
33:
All I can do is continue to cling onto
the legacy you've left us. To try to
pick up the pieces.
36:
I see. I was right after all, Adjudicus.
You could never become the Lord of
Shadow.
43:
I only ever did as you taught me,
Uncle.
51:
Let's return home! We must bring
news of this to the people of the
land!
67:
It's you! You... you've been here the
whole time?
70:
Were you watching? I... I've grown
stronger, haven't I? Both as a warrior,
and as a ruler.
74:
There's no need to worry about me
anymore!
77:
Even without you here, I can...
I can...
85:
What am I saying? I can't go on
without you, Shakari!
88:
I... I couldn't do anything! All the
kindnesses, the aid, the love... How
could I repay it all?
90:
I wanted to reach the same heights
as you, to proudly stand by your
sideas equals!
92:
To hold your hand and express to
you the gratitude I feel.
102:
You were so determinedso
stubborn in your ways. I held your
hands, in those brief moments while
you slept.
112:
No! Please, stay by my side!
DON'T LEAVE ME!
132:
These tears you shed are not in vain.
But I implore you, Lilith Stratos. Look
below.
138:
Lilith! Look at all the people on the
surface! The refugees, everyone is
down there!
143:
And the elves... standing alongside
fiends!
146:
That would be the work of the troops
I led. It seems the elves have proven
their worth after all.
149:
But we still have much left to do. We
must continue to pave the way
forward, to put an end to the strife
between our people.
156:
You shall have my aid wherever you
need it. But first, we must leave this
place behind us.
158: Come, Lilith. Your people await you.
